{"source_key":"sha256-c8597aca71664a84bdd657ea13dadbd3","record_index":140,"record_hash":"sha256:db7d8b6a5976fbeea9fb7a6854ca4b72f8b0fbc942c74132b7a2ab459b8b349c","timestamp":"2026-05-20T00:59:32.992Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"The doc is directionally right. `but-agentlog` is still at the flat POC stage: session plus deduped transcript records, with explicit whole-session association only. The “turn” layer, environment snapshots, indexes, provider turn grouping, and turn-scoped relationships are not implemented yet.\n\n**Where We Stand**\nCurrent flow:\n\n- [capture.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:13) snapshots the transcript file and derives `session_key` / `source_key`.\n- [transcript.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:20) parses provider records into normalized `ParsedRecord`s.\n- [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:55) dedupes via `:record-hashes`.\n- [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:110) appends transcript records and hashes atomically, but only those two edits.\n- [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:118) can explicitly attach a session to a GitMeta target with `gitbutler:agent-sessions`.\n\nSo the doc’s implementation notes are accurate: the missing thing is preserving the batch boundary after dedupe. The code already has `source_key`, `record_index`, and `record_hash`, which are exactly the ingredients needed for turn membership.\n\n**Important Catch**\nGitMeta’s current atomic batch API only supports list append and set add. It does not support scalar `set`/record writes inside `apply_edits`. That matters because [Including-turns.md](/Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02%[REDACTED:entropy].md:167) wants transcript records, hashes, turn object, turn list entry, and indexes as one logical update.\n\nMy opinion: don’t design a repair path first. Either extend GitMeta `MetaEdit` to support scalar set, or store the first turn detail entirely as list/set-friendly data. Repair logic for missing turns sounds like annoying archaeology we can avoid.\n\n**Decisions I’d Make**\n- Turn key: use `sha256-hex16(session_key + NUL + source_key + NUL + ordered_new_record_hashes)`.\n- Turn membership: store ordered objects, not just hashes:\n  `[{ \"source_key\", \"record_index\", \"record_hash\" }]`.\n- Previous turn pointer: skip it for v1. The `:turns` list order plus capture timestamp is enough, and a pointer adds race-prone bookkeeping.\n- Provider turn key: add optional top-level `provider_turn_key` to transcript records, hashed/redacted. Useful for display, never identity.\n- Checked-out refs: don’t make this a separate durable field. Model plain Git as a one-stack/one-branch snapshot and mark the entrypoint branch there.\n- Path cap: pick a boring number now, like 256 paths per list, with `count` and `truncated`. Add commit count caps too, because branch snapshots can explode.\n- Index values: don’t store only `turn-key`. Store a resolvable ref like `session_key + \"/\" + turn_key`; otherwise index lookup can find a turn but not cheaply resolve its session.\n- Index keys: hash branch/review/change key material for GitMeta key safety, while storing readable names/ids inside the turn snapshot.\n\n**Useful Existing Code To Steal**\n[eval_hook.rs]([REDACTED:entropy].rs:58) already captures a lightweight repo snapshot: uncommitted files via `but_core::diff::worktree_changes_no_renames`, and stacks via `but_workspace::head_info`. That’s basically the seed of the environment snapshot, though `but-agentlog` currently avoids those heavier dependencies.\n\n**Open Questions Worth Keeping**\nThe real unresolved ones are:\n\n- Should `but-agentlog` depend directly on `but_ctx`/`but_workspace`, or should the outer `but` command collect environment snapshots and pass them in?\n- Do we extend GitMeta atomic edits now, or constrain turn storage to list/set operations?\n- What exact branch/review/change index value format do we want so lookup is cheap and rebuildable?\n- What is the first relationship shape for optional turn scope on confirmed associations?\n- Do we want commit file lists in v1, or just branch/change/review observation plus worktree files first?\n\nMy recommended next doc update: replace the broad “Gaps To Resolve” section with these as decisions/defaults, and add a concrete v1 storage shape. No code changes made yet, so I didn’t run tests.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T00:59:32.992Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}